values: To judge something is to say if it is good or bad.
The boy was going to judge how his mother’s turkey tasted.

To judge is to form an opinion or make a decision about someone or something based on certain criteria or evidence.
A judge is a person appointed or elected to decide on legal matters in a court of law.
